Elite Edimmu are level 90 Slayer creatures found in the Edimmu resource dungeon in Prifddinas. They can only be fought while on a slayer assignment (unless using Slayer Wildcards), and will randomly spawn while fighting normal edimmu. In addition, it can only be attacked by the player it is after, and nobody else for three minutes. Edimmu are assigned by Duradel/Lapalok, Kuradal, Morvran and Laniakea. They can also be killed under several cluster assignments, such as undead, ghosts, zombies, and Creatures of Daemonheim, effectively adding Jacquelyn and The Raptor as slayer masters that can assign edimmu. They attack with both magic and melee, and will heal 25% of the damage they deal. Their ashes can be collected in an infernal urn.

Elite spawn rates can be further increased with the use of fellstalk incense sticks and tier 3 luck. Elite edimmu are larger than normal edimmu (being a 2x2 monster compared to 1x1), deal more damage and attack a tick faster than them. Elite edimmu have a greater chance of dropping blood necklace shards and are the only monsters to drop an edimmu pet.

As only elite edimmu can drop the edimmu pet, which is an item in the Slayer collection log, players can use Jacquelyn's short tasks to fight many elite edimmus under the ghosts and zombies cluster tasks. Slayer Introspection can be used to lower the assignment count to 15 and the Slayer master cape perk can be used alongside slayer points to skip tasks until a ghosts or zombies tasks is assigned. At least one elite monster is guaranteed to spawn in a slayer task, this effectively lets the player fight at least 1 elite edimmu every 15 edimmu kills. NPC Contact can be used to minimize travel and teleport time.

Unlike their weaker brethren, elite edimmu do not have any weaknesses but still share the same affinities as them, making ranged the strongest, magic moderate, and melee the weakest against them.

During combat, other normal edimmu have a higher chance of aggroing to the player, which can often cause the player to become overwhelmed, especially at melee distance.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 29 August 2023 (Update):
    • Fixed an issue with Elite Edimmus not playing their death animation.
  • patch 17 April 2023 (Update):
    • Fixed the issue of incorrect souls being captured by Ushabti.
  • patch 11 April 2023 (Update):
    • Edimmu will work for Ghost, Zombie and Undead Slayer tasks.
  • patch 3 August 2015 (Update):
    • Powerful edimmu will now occasionally drop attuned crystal weapon and armour seeds.
  • patch 18 May 2015 (Update):
    • Edimmus can now walk and attack at the same time.
  • update 10 November 2014 (Update):
    • Added to game.
